{"id": "EUVD-2024-53828", "enisaUuid": "a8dab482-b5b6-39f2-a64d-907e72f63068", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nksmbd: fix a missing return value check bug\n\nIn the smb2_send_interim_resp(), if ksmbd_alloc_work_struct()\nfails to allocate a node, it returns a NULL pointer to the\nin_work pointer. This can lead to an illegal memory write of\nin_work->response_buf when allocate_interim_rsp_buf() attempts\nto perform a kzalloc() on it.\n\nTo address this issue, incorporating a check for the return\nvalue of ksmbd_alloc_work_struct() ensures that the function\nreturns immediately upon allocation failure, thereby preventing\nthe aforementioned illegal memory access.", "datePublished": "2025-01-19T12:31:27", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T21:32:14", "baseScore": 7.1, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/781c743e18bfd9b7dc0383f036ae952bd1486f21", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ee7e40f7fb17f08a8cbae50553e5c2e10ae32fce", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/271ae0edbfc942795c162e6cf20d2bc02bd7fde4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2976e91a3e569cf2c92c9f71512c0ab1312fe965", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4c16e1cadcbcaf3c82d5fc310fbd34d0f5d0db7c", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-57925", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/03/msg00001.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-57925"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.06, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "08ec5333-ccf8-3212-86e0-e1c6d9a96407", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6f0207218c4c125f5bf32055ac4220b4ef3b7e67 <781c743e18bfd9b7dc0383f036ae952bd1486f21"}, {"id": "3edea462-4c18-3ca9-83a5-808172122b85", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13"}, {"id": "5b9fc940-7b04-3feb-9c90-30bc22d473a2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "041bba4414cda37d00063952c9bff9c3d5812a19 <4c16e1cadcbcaf3c82d5fc310fbd34d0f5d0db7c"}, {"i